# Don’t ask AI to build the house. Ask it to help you lay one brick at a time—while you inspect every brick.

1) Treat  AI/copiolot as a thinking partner, not a code vending machine.

1)First describe the requirement, dont try to build the code in 1 attempt, AI will give big large code not easy to understand.

2) If the code is in chunks its easy to understand and easy to debug , do changes .

3) So, try to break down the requirement in to pieces

4) so that we can check for working for non working solutions.

5) Document each step and then execute the code in steps and check for outputs.

6) In the process of doing coding with AI in above steps we understand what works what does not work.
      
   Exam- python can not read folders, pyspark can.
         Checking data types of each column if required
         checking if any negative values , null values

7)Make each step by step requirement documented so that It will be easy to track and helps in acheveing expected results
